---
import ToolLayout from '../../components/ToolLayout.astro';
---
<ToolLayout title="Grout Calculator" description="Calculate how much grout you need for your tile installation project." icon="ðŸ”³" category="Material Calculators" categorySlug="material-calculators">
  <div slot="calculator">
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <div><label class="block text-sm font-semibold text-[#1B4965] mb-1">Area (sq ft)</label><input type="number" id="area" value="80" min="1" class="w-full border border-gray-300 rounded-lg px-4 py-2 focus:ring-2 focus:ring-[#FF6B35] focus:border-transparent" /></div>
      <div><label class="block text-sm font-semibold text-[#1B4965] mb-1">Tile Length (inches)</label><input type="number" id="tl" value="12" min="1" class="w-full border border-gray-300 rounded-lg px-4 py-2 focus:ring-2 focus:ring-[#FF6B35] focus:border-transparent" /></div>
      <div><label class="block text-sm font-semibold text-[#1B4965] mb-1">Tile Width (inches)</label><input type="number" id="tw" value="12" min="1" class="w-full border border-gray-300 rounded-lg px-4 py-2 focus:ring-2 focus:ring-[#FF6B35] focus:border-transparent" /></div>
      <div><label class="block text-sm font-semibold text-[#1B4965] mb-1">Tile Thickness (inches)</label><input type="number" id="tt" value="0.375" min="0.1" step="0.125" class="w-full border border-gray-300 rounded-lg px-4 py-2 focus:ring-2 focus:ring-[#FF6B35] focus:border-transparent" /></div>
      <div><label class="block text-sm font-semibold text-[#1B4965] mb-1">Joint Width (inches)</label>
        <select id="jw" class="w-full border border-gray-300 rounded-lg px-4 py-2 focus:ring-2 focus:ring-[#FF6B35]">
          <option value="0.0625">1/16"</option>
          <option value="0.125" selected>1/8"</option>
          <option value="0.1875">3/16"</option>
          <option value="0.25">1/4"</option>
          <option value="0.375">3/8"</option>
          <option value="0.5">1/2"</option>
        </select>
      </div>
    </div>
    <button onclick="calc()" class="mt-6 bg-[#FF6B35] hover:bg-[#e55a2b] text-white font-semibold px-8 py-3 rounded-lg transition-colors w-full md:w-auto">Calculate Grout</button>
    <div id="result" class="mt-6 hidden"><div class="bg-[#1B4965]/5 rounded-xl p-6"><h3 class="font-bold text-[#1B4965] text-lg mb-3">Results</h3><div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4" id="res"></div></div></div>
  </div>
  <Fragment slot="content">
    <h2>How Grout is Calculated</h2>
    <p>Grout volume depends on tile size, joint width, and tile thickness. The formula calculates the volume of all grout joints per square foot, then multiplies by coverage area. Standard grout coverage is about 1 lb per sq ft for 12Ã—12 tiles with 1/8" joints.</p>
    <h2>Grout Types</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Unsanded grout</strong>: For joints 1/8" or narrower</li>
      <li><strong>Sanded grout</strong>: For joints wider than 1/8"</li>
      <li><strong>Epoxy grout</strong>: Waterproof, stain-resistant, more expensive</li>
    </ul>
  </Fragment>
</ToolLayout>
<script is:inline>
function calc(){
  const area=parseFloat(document.getElementById('area').value);
  const tl=parseFloat(document.getElementById('tl').value);const tw=parseFloat(document.getElementById('tw').value);
  const tt=parseFloat(document.getElementById('tt').value);const jw=parseFloat(document.getElementById('jw').value);
  // Grout volume formula: area * ((tl+tw)/(tl*tw)) * jw * tt * 144 cubic inches per sqft, then convert to lbs (1 cu in grout â‰ˆ 0.04 lbs)
  const groutVolPerSqFt=((tl+tw)/(tl*tw))*jw*tt*144;
  const totalVolCuIn=groutVolPerSqFt*area;
  const lbs=totalVolCuIn*0.04;
  const bags25=Math.ceil(lbs/25);
  document.getElementById('result').classList.remove('hidden');
  document.getElementById('res').innerHTML=`
    <div class="text-center"><div class="text-3xl font-bold text-[#FF6B35]">${lbs.toFixed(1)} lbs</div><div class="text-sm text-gray-500">Grout Needed</div></div>
    <div class="text-center"><div class="text-3xl font-bold text-[#FF6B35]">${bags25}</div><div class="text-sm text-gray-500">25-lb Bags</div></div>`;
}
</script>
